UNITED NATIONS - Major General Jean-Paul Deconinck of Belgium has been appointed as commander of the peacekeeping force in Mali, the UN's most dangerous mission, the UN announced on Thursday.Deconinck replaced Major General Michael Lollesgaard of Denmark who was force commander for a year.READ: Mali soldiers killed by landmineThe 13,000-strong peacekeeping operation, known as MINUSMA, has repeatedly been targeted in attacks.More than 100 peacekeepers have been killed since the mission was established in 2013.Mali regained control of the north after a French-led military intervention in January 2013 drove out jihadists, but insurgents remain active across large parts of the region.AFP